-------------------------------------------------------------------------
		        How to run:
		===========================
1) From linux terminal change directory to folder containing source code
	cd <path>
2) Remove any existing binary if present by using the following command
	make clean
3) Compile the source code using make command
	make
4) Run the mydraw.out executable file created
	./music_box

-------------------------------------------------------------------------
		    Modes:
		============

----------------
Lights:
-----------------
    W ---Toggle Wall light
    L ---Toggle table lamp

--------------------------------------
Box and human and scene movements: 
--------------------------------------
(Press the given key to perform rotation 
on the given part. Rotation keys are mentioned below)

    I ---Initial Position for all parts
    | ---Human
    [ ---Box
    s ---Scene

    t ---Torso
    n ---Neck
    h ---Head

    q ---Left Upper Arm
    w ---Left Lower Arm
    e ---Left Hand

    p ---Right Upper Arm
    o ---Right Lower Arm
    i ---Right Hand

    z ---Left Upper Leg
    c ---Left Lower Leg
    a ---Left Foot

    m ---Right Upper Leg
    b ---Right Lower Leg
    l ---Right Foot 

*Legs and arms shortcut are related to keyboard layout of alphabets. 


		Rotation Controls:
	   ===========================

    0 	---Initial position for selected part
    1,2 ---X axis
    3,4 ---Y axis
    5,6 ---Z axis
    7,8 ---Open/close box 
-------------------------------------------------------------------------

*******SAMPLE RUN********
--------------------------

1. Use Up arrow key to move close to box. Press '[' to select box. Press 7,8 to open or close music box and 1,2,3,4,5,6 to rotate box. Press '|' to select doll. Again 1-6 can be used to perform rotation. Similarly, other body parts can be selected and rotated as mentioned in Mode.

